ger（中）和 Stevie Wonder（右）的三张并排照片" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/TheRollingStones-Lady-Gaga-Stevie-Wonder-collaboration-preview-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>预览了他们与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lady-gaga">Lady Gaga</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>合作的新单曲 - 请听下面的剪辑。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-rolling-stones-new-album-release-date-hackney-diamonds-3494545">滚石乐队的回归带来了更大的冲击</a></strong></li></ul><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-confirm-new-album-hackney-diamonds-and-single-angry-3494112">这支传奇乐队于 9 月 6 日宣布推出他们的第 24 张录音室专辑“Hackney Diamonds”</a> ，并分享了其主打单曲“Angry”。继 2005 年的<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-the-rolling-stones-7763-312997#:~:text=This%20is%20an%20old%2Dfashioned,well%20be%20by%20Sheryl%20Crow.">《A Bigger Bang》</a>之后，这张唱片将标志着滚石乐队 18 年来首张原创音乐合集。</p><p>本月早些时候，据透露， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-hackney-diamonds-features-paul-mccartney-lady-gaga-elton-john-and-stevie-wonder-3498112">Gaga 和 Wonder 都创作了一首名为“Sweet Sounds Of Heaven”的歌曲</a>。两人将与<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-says-paul-mccartney-really-rocked-it-on-rolling-stones-collaboration-3502352">保罗·麦卡特尼</a>、<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/elton-john">埃尔顿·约翰</a>和前滚石乐队贝斯手比尔·怀曼一起出现在“Hackney Diamonds”节目中。</p><p>现在，滚石乐队在社交媒体上分享了一段 16 秒的《Sweet Sounds Of Heaven》片段，并宣布该曲目将于英国夏令时本周四（9 月 28 日）下午 5 点作为单曲发行。<a href="https://therollingstones.lnk.to/SweetSoundsOfHeaven" target="_blank" rel="noopener">您可以在此处预先保存/预先添加</a>。</p><p>在这里查看预告片：</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">天籁之音<br />与<a href="https://twitter.com/ladygaga?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@ladygaga</a>和 Stevie Wonder 一起<br />英国夏令时 9 月 28 日下午 5 点坠落到地球<br />预保存/预添加： <a href="https://t.co/f1Odn2p9Wm">https://t.co/f1Odn2p9Wm</a> <a href="https://t.co/OyO6ZvwAkP">pic.twitter.com/OyO6ZvwAkP</a></p><p> — 滚石乐队 (@RollingStones) <a href="https://twitter.com/RollingStones/status/1706421319561073129?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 25 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>在其他新闻中，主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mick-jagger">米克·贾格尔</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mick-jagger-says-paul-mccartney-really-rocked-it-on-rolling-stones-collaboration-3502352">在接受采访时解释了披头士乐队偶像麦卡特尼是如何加入“哈克尼钻石”的</a>。</p><p> “我们建议他演奏这首朋克曲调，”贾格尔回忆道。 “我不知道结果如何，但他真的很震撼，而且他喜欢这样做。他说：“和乐队一起演奏真是太棒了！和乐队一起演奏真的很愉快。”</p><p> “Hackney Diamonds” 将于 10 月 20 日以各种格式发布 -<a href="https://therollingstones.lnk.to/HackneyDiamondsPR" target="_blank" rel="noopener">您可以在此处预订/预保存</a>。</p><p>该项目在多个地点录制，包括洛杉矶的 Henson Recording Studios、伦敦的 Metropolis Studios、巴哈马的 Sanctuary Studios、Electric Lady Studios 和纽约的 The Hit Factory/Germano Studios。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="滚石乐队 - 愤怒（官方视频）" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_mEC54eTuGw?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “我不想傲慢，但如果我们不是真的喜欢这张专辑，我们就不会发行它，”贾格尔在本月早些时候的一次直播会议上解释道。 “我们说我们必须制作一张我们真正爱自己的唱片。</p><p> “我们对此非常满意。我们并不自以为是，但希望大家喜欢。”</p><p>在谈话的其他地方，在主持人吉米·法伦问他们这是否是“一种俚语”后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-explain-meaning-of-new-hackney-diamonds-album-name-3494480">，乐队解释了唱片标题背后的含义</a>。</p><p>滚石乐队的最新专辑于 2016 年以蓝调翻唱唱片<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/rolling-stones-blue-lonesome-1882686#:~:text=These%2012%20tracks%20were%20recorded,but%20not%20wanting%20for%20thrills.">《Blue &amp; Lonesome》</a>的形式推出。</p><p>与此同时， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-are-already-working-on-their-next-album-3498047">贾格尔证实该团队已经开始制作下一部完整作品</a>。</p></div><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-preview-lady-gaga-and-stevie-wonder-collaboration-3504215">滚石乐队预览 Lady Gaga 和 Stevie Wonder 合作的帖子本周</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
艾德·汤森庄园退出艾德·希兰的“大声思考”抄袭案https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-townsend-estate-withdraws-ed-sheeran-thinking-out-loud-copyright-plagiarism-case-3504048?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=ed-townsend-遗产撤回埃德·希兰大声思考版权抄袭案Surej SinghTue, 26 Sep 2023 08:32:05 +0000 Music NewsNewsPop https://www.nme.com/?p=3504048 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>上诉的撤回禁止埃德·汤森的遗产委员会稍后重新提交案件</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-townsend-estate-withdraws-ed-sheeran-thinking-out-loud-copyright-plagiarism-case-3504048">埃德·汤森 (Ed Townsend) 遗产管理委员会从艾德·希兰 (Ed Sheeran) 的《Thinking Out Loud》抄袭案中撤回的消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>艾德·汤森 (Ed Townsend) 遗产管理委员会已正式撤回对<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ed-sheeran">艾德·希兰 (Ed Sheeran)</a>长达数年的抄袭诉讼的上诉，该诉讼于 2016 年首次提起， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-wins-thinking-out-loud-plagiarism-case-3439493">似乎在 5 月份结束</a>，希兰获得了胜利。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/ed-sheeran-review-subtract-lyrics-3439379">艾德·希兰 (Ed Sheeran) – “Subtract”评论：他的困难时期暴露无遗</a></strong></li></ul><p>今年 5 月，埃德·汤森<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-2-1195464">(Ed Townsend) 的继承人于 2016 年提起</a>诉讼，指控希兰抄袭了马文·盖伊 (Marvin Gaye) 的《Let&#39;s Get It On》，该案被宣告无罪。</p><p>判决后，汤森的继承人宣布打算上诉重审。然而，现在根据<a href="https://fingfx.thomsonreuters.com/gfx/legaldocs/zdpxrqwlgpx/COPYRIGHT%20SHEERAN%20THINKING%20appeal.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">法庭文件</a>显示，遗产管理机构已撤回上诉，使其无法在以后重新提起诉讼，这使得艾德·希兰在该案中获得了明确的胜诉。</p><p> <a href="https://www.reuters.com/legal/lets-get-it-on-songwriters-estate-drops-ed-sheeran-copyright-verdict-appeal-2023-09-21/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>路透社</em></a>也证实了撤诉，艾德·希兰的律师艾琳·法卡斯告诉该刊物，汤森德的遗产管理机构“认识到上诉最终会导致判决得到维持，但他们也会面临法律费用和成本，因此明智地撤回了。” </p><figure id="attachment_3504177" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3504177" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3504177" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/ed-sheeran-court@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3504177" class="wp-caption-text"> 2023 年 5 月，艾德·希兰在法庭外向媒体发表讲话。图片来源：Alexi J. Rosenfeld/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-wins-thinking-out-loud-plagiarism-case-3439493">五月判决后，希兰在法庭外对记者表示</a>：“我显然对案件的结果非常满意，看起来<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-warns-hell-quit-music-if-found-guilty-in-copyright-trial-3438272">我终于不必从日常工作中退休了</a>……”但与此同时，我对这样毫无根据的指控被允许诉诸法庭感到难以置信的沮丧。”</p><p>五月判决后，希兰发行了他的最新专辑“-”（“减法”）。这张专辑获得<em>NME</em>的尼克·莱文 (Nick Levine) 的<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/ed-sheeran-review-subtract-lyrics-3439379">三星级评论</a>。莱文写道：“大多数‘-’都是固执的单一节奏，这是德斯纳柔和的制作风格的一个常见缺点。如果有些地方变得有点相同，可以说这是希兰当时正在解决的心理健康问题的真实反映。当然，他的一些抒情的副歌——破碎的波浪、落下的眼泪——增加了这样的印象：‘-’是这位艺术家处于特别低潮的心态的未经过滤的快照。”</p><p>这位创作歌手接下来计划发行一张即将发行<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-announces-second-new-album-of-2023-autumn-variations-3488184">的专辑“Autumn Variations”</a> 。这张专辑将是他今年的第二张专辑，继五月份的“-”（“Subtract”）之后。这张新专辑将于 9 月 29 日通过他自己的 Gingerbread Man Records 发行，与《Subtract》一样，它是由<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-national">The National</a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/aaron-dessner">Aaron Dessner</a>制作的。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-townsend-estate-withdraws-ed-sheeran-thinking-out-loud-copyright-plagiarism-case-3504048">埃德·汤森 (Ed Townsend) 遗产管理委员会从艾德·希兰 (Ed Sheeran) 的《Thinking Out Loud》抄袭案中撤回的消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
